@database "Guidelines Guide"
@author "Heiko Schr—der"
@$VER: 3.0 (Release 3)
@wordwrap

@node Main "Guidelines V1.1 for FW 97"
                               @{" < Table of Contents " link "Macro-Package.guide/Main"}

         !!! This macro needs at least "Final Writer 97" !!!

@{fg shine}Advantage:@{fg text}
   FW 97 allows you to use guidelines.
   But the programmers forgot to add a possibility to create multiple guidelines
   at once that are arranged with a specific spacing. 
   This macro now fills this gap.

@{fg shine}Requirements:@{fg text}
   "Final Writer 97" or better

@{fg shine}Using the @{"macro" system "Sys:Utilities/Multiview Guidelines.iff"}:@{fg text}

   A@{fg fill}r@{fg text}range
      Choose the type of the needed guidelines
         - horizontal
         - vertical

   @{fg fill}N@{fg text}umber:
      Enter here how many guidelines you want to create.

   O@{fg fill}f@{fg text}fset:
      Determines the starting point of the 1st guideline.

   @{fg fill}S@{fg text}pacing:
      Enter here the preferred space between two guidelines.

                     - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 

   @{fg fill}A@{fg text}pply
      Create the guidelines using the actual settings.

   @{fg fill}C@{fg text}ancel
   @{fg fill}ESC@{fg text} or close window
      Quits the macro.

                     - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 

@{fg shine}Hint:@{fg text}
   If you only need one guideline, use "Offset" to determine the position of it
   and leave "Spacing" blank.

@endnode
